In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add the egg, chocolate and coffee; mix well. Combine the flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in coconut. Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 in. apart onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 375 degrees F for 12-15 minutes or until edges are browned. Remove to wire racks to cool. For frosting, combine the chocolate, sour cream and butter in a small mixing bowl. Add enough sugar to achieve spreading consistency. Frost cooled cookies. Sprinkle with coconut.